{
  "message": "test(conformance): add FP-P2D-129 IO round-trip fixtures + packet filter test\n\nAdds seven IO round-trip fixture packets and the matching test that\nruns them through the packet-filter entry point.\n\ncrates/fp-conformance/fixtures/packets/fp_p2d_129_*.json:\n\n- fp_p2d_129_json_round_trip_columns_strict: DataFrame.to_json /\n  read_json round-trip with orient=\"columns\".\n- fp_p2d_129_json_round_trip_records_strict: same, orient=\"records\".\n- fp_p2d_129_jsonl_round_trip_basic_strict: DataFrame.to_json /\n  read_json with lines=True.\n- fp_p2d_129_parquet_round_trip_basic_strict: parquet writer /\n  reader round-trip.\n- fp_p2d_129_feather_round_trip_basic_strict: feather writer /\n  reader round-trip.\n- fp_p2d_129_excel_round_trip_basic_strict: xlsx writer / reader\n  round-trip.\n- fp_p2d_129_ipc_stream_round_trip_basic_strict: Arrow IPC stream\n  writer / reader round-trip.\n\nEach fixture carries its input as json_input (for the text formats)\nor as a base64 blob in *_input_base64 (for the binary formats),\nmatching the PacketFixture fields added earlier in this series,\nand targets the matching JsonRoundTrip / JsonlRoundTrip /\nParquetRoundTrip / FeatherRoundTrip / ExcelRoundTrip /\nIpcStreamRoundTrip FixtureOperation variant.\n\ncrates/fp-conformance/src/lib.rs:\n\n- Adds packet_filter_runs_io_round_trip_packet, a unit test that\n  calls run_packet_by_id(&cfg, \"FP-P2D-129\", OracleMode::Fixture-\n  Expected) and asserts the report is green with at least five\n  fixtures. This confirms the packet-filter path correctly selects\n  the new FP-P2D-129 packet and that the six round-trip operations\n  execute end-to-end through the oracle-driven fixture runner.",
